The paper deals with geometric problems and algorithms for uncertain and indecisive points, which are common topics in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of probability distributions and the development of shape inclusion probability functions suggest a connection to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithms for computing distributions and LP-type problems involve probabilistic and statistical techniques, which could also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the use of randomized and deterministic algorithms suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
